{{Quote|And I thought they smelled bad...on the outside.|[[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]|audio=TauntaunSmell.flac|<ref name="Episode 5">{{Film|V}}</ref>}}
'''Giant tauntauns''', also referred to as '''common tauntauns''' due to their abundance, were the largest of the [[Tauntaun/Legends|tauntaun]] subspecies on [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]]. [[File:Tauntaunrest-woswfg.jpg|thumb|left|180px|A resting giant tauntaun.]] They could measure 15 feet long and nearly 8 1/2 feet tall. A healthy adult had only one known predator, the dreaded [[Wampa/Legends|wampa]]. They were themselves omnivores, eating fungi such as floor [[Lichen/Legends|lichen]] as well as [[Ice scrabbler/Legends|ice scrabblers]] and [[Hoth hog/Legends|Hoth hogs]].

They were stubborn creatures, but made ideal patrol mounts for the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance's]] [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] in the absence of [[Repulsorcraft/Legends|repulsorcraft]], which were unreliable in Hoth's extremely cold climate. Personnel such as [[Corporal/Legends|Corporal]] [[Vyn Rolado/Legends|Vyn Rolado]] were responsible for taming the alpha female of a tauntaun pack, in turn allowing the Alliance to easily train the remainder of the pack.

Several of the creatures were taken to the pole of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] for pleasure riding.

{{Creature-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The creatures were represented on screen through a combination of puppetry and stop-motion animation.
They are also used as a mount in Star Wars Battlefront and ''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II]]'' but have a very broad head in the games and are easily killed with rockets.

